title: What's New Pussycat (1965) (Peter Sellers, Peter O'Toole)
description:
WHAT'S NEW PUSSYCAT - 1965

  What's New Pussycat is a sex comedy that's actually quite funny, in its own bizarre way. It's deemed politically incorrect now, and back when it first opened American movie critics lambasted it as immoral & decadent. Not much has changed. 

  Enjoy! It was the '60s. Things didn't have to make sense.

  The story centers around the very complicated love life of the character Michael James (Peter O'Toole), who is trying to stop seeing other women so that he can focus on the one woman he really loves, Carol (Romy Schneider). To help him overcome his sexual addictions, he seeks professional help from the pschotherapist Dr. Fritz Fassbender (Peter Sellers). Unfortuneately, Dr. Fassbander is a sex-crazed nut in pursuit of patient Renee (Capucine). Written by Woody Allen.

  Starring:  Peter Sellers, Peter O'Toole, Romy Schneider, Capucine, Paula Prentiss, Ursula Andress, Woody Allen.

  Directed by: Clive Donner.

  Quality: Very Good Xvid from DVD.

  Length: 1hr. 44min.

  Language: English.

  Size: 720 x 448
